";a:27:{s:4:"name";s:26:"YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp";s:4:"slug";s:26:"yith-woocommerce-mailchimp";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.1.1";s:6:"author";s:43:"<a href="http://yithemes.com/">Yithemes</a>";s:14:"author_profile";s:39:"https://profiles.wordpress.org/yithemes";s:8:"requires";s:3:"4.0";s:6:"tested";s:5:"4.8.3";s:12:"requires_php";b:0;s:6:"rating";d:88;s:7:"ratings";a:5:{i:5;i:6;i:4;i:0;i:3;i:0;i:2;i:0;i:1;i:1;}s:11:"num_ratings";i:7;s:15:"support_threads";i:1;s:24:"support_threads_resolved";i:1;s:15:"active_installs";i:1000;s:10:"downloaded";i:19624;s:12:"last_updated";s:21:"2017-10-25 2:23pm GMT";s:5:"added";s:10:"2015-03-26";s:8:"homepage";s:62:"http://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/";s:8:"sections";a:5:{s:11:"description";s:1811:"<p>Get perfect integration of MailChimp into your e-commerce. An opportunity to let you benefit from all advantages that an email marketing service provider offers, so that you can manage contacts from your shop in an easy and almost automatic way and create specific campaigns for your target customers. The more targeted and specific campaigns are conceived, the higher is conversion rate of your email campaign. With YITH WooCommerce MailChimp you can manage users’ subscriptions directly from your e-commerce.</p>\n<h4>Возможности:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Customers&#8217; subscription to a specific list in MailChimp:</li>\n<li>Subscription can be either automatic or require customer&#8217;s consent in checkout page.</li>\n<li>Subscription can be either made when order is placed or when order is completed.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Варианты</h3>\n<p>If you have suggestions about how to improve YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp, you can <a href="mailto:&#112;&#108;&#x75;&#x67;&#x69;&#x6e;&#x73;&#064;&#121;&#105;&#116;&#104;&#x65;&#x6d;&#x65;&#x73;&#x2e;&#099;&#111;&#109;" title="Your Inspiration Themes" rel="nofollow">write us</a> so we can bundle them into YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp.</p>\n<h3>Переводчики</h3>\n<h4>Доступные языки</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>English (Default)</li>\n<li>Italian</li>\n<li>Spanish</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Need to translate this plugin into your own language? You can contribute to its translation from <a href="https://translate.wordpress.org/projects/wp-plugins/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp" title="Translating WordPress" rel="nofollow">this page</a>.<br />\nYour help is precious! Thanks</p>\n<h3>Документацию к плагину</h3>\n<p>Full documentation is available <a href="http://yithemes.com/docs-plugins/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp" rel="nofollow">here</a>.</p>\n";s:12:"installation";s:415:"<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp</code> from Plugins page</li>\n</ol>\n<p>YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp will add a new submenu called &#171;Mailchimp&#187; under &#171;YIT Plugins&#187; menu. Here you are able to configure all the plugin settings.</p>\n";s:3:"faq";s:1270:"\n<h4>Installation Instructions</h4>\n<p>\n<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp</code> from Plugins page</li>\n</ol>\n<p>YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp will add a new submenu called &#171;Mailchimp&#187; under &#171;YIT Plugins&#187; menu. Here you are able to configure all the plugin settings.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Where can I find my API key</h4>\n<p>\n<p>You just have to register on mailchimp.com and visit the following <a href="http://admin.mailchimp.com/account/api/" title="Account page" rel="nofollow">page</a></p>\n</p>\n<h4>Is it possible to subscribe users automatically?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Sure, you just have to select the list in which you want to register the users, and deactivate the visualization of the &#171;newsletter subscription&#187; checkbox.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Is it possible to subscribe users at the &#171;order complete&#187; stage?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Sure, you just have to select the voice &#171;Order completed&#187; in the &#171;Register after&#187; option.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>I can&#8217;t see my list in the dedicated list table</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Try to press the &#171;Update lists&#187; button near the select</p>\n</p>\n\n";s:9:"changelog";s:2667:"<h4>1.1.1 &#8212; Released: Oct, 25 &#8212; 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: WooCommerce 3.2.1 support</li>\n<li>New: WordPress 4.8.2 support</li>\n<li>New: update internal plugin-fw</li>\n<li>Tweak: avoided double form handler execution, adding return false at the end of handler</li>\n<li>Dev: created subscribe wrapper for subscription process and refactored code</li>\n<li>Dev: moved cachable requests init to init hook, to let third party code filter them</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.0 &#8212; Released: May, 05 &#8212; 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Add: WooCommerce 3.0.x compatibility</li>\n<li>Add: WordPress 4.7.4 compatibility</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.9 &#8212; Released: Nov, 28 &#8212; 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Add: spanish translation</li>\n<li>Add: italian translation</li>\n<li>Tweak: changed text domain to yith-woocommerce-mailchimp</li>\n<li>Tweak: updated plugin-fw version</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.8 &#8212; Released: Jun, 13 &#8212; 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: WooCommerce 2.6-RC1 support</li>\n<li>Tweak: improved performance with last plugin-fw version</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.7 &#8212; Released: Apr, 26 &#8212; 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: warnings related to partial plugin.fw on wp.org repo</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.6 &#8212; Released: Apr, 12 &#8212; 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: WooCommerce 2.5.5 compatibility</li>\n<li>Added: WordPress 4.5 compatibility</li>\n<li>Tweak: Updated internal plugin-fw</li>\n<li>Fixed: lists/list call now retrieves all lists, and not only first page</li>\n<li>Fixed: checkout checkbox position option, causing unexpected results</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.5 &#8212; Released: Dec, 14 &#8212; 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: check over MailChimp class existence, to avoid Fatal Error with other plugins including that class</li>\n<li>Added: MailChimp error translation via .po archives</li>\n<li>Tweak: improved plugin import procedure</li>\n<li>Tweak: Updated internal plugin-fw</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.4 &#8212; Released: Oct, 23 &#8212; 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tweak: Performance improved with new plugin core 2.0</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.3 &#8212; Released: Aug, 12 &#8212; 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: Compatibility with WC 2.4.2</li>\n<li>Tweak: Updated internal plugin-fw</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2 &#8212; Released: May, 04 &#8212; 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: WP 4.2.1 support</li>\n<li>Fixed: &#171;Plugin Documentation&#187; appearing on all plugins</li>\n<li>Fixed: various minor bug</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1 &#8212; Released: Apr, 20 &#8212; 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: delete key-related options/transient when key changed</li>\n<li>Tweak: string revision</li>\n<li>Fixed: various minor bug</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0 &#8212; Released: Mar, 26 &#8212; 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Релиз первой версии плагина.</li>\n</ul>\n";s:11:"screenshots";s:969:"<ol><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-2.png?rev=1752588"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-2.png?rev=1752588" alt="The YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp settings page (checkout)"></a><p>The YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp settings page (checkout)</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-1.png?rev=1752588"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-1.png?rev=1752588" alt="The YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp settings page (integration)"></a><p>The YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp settings page (integration)</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-3.png?rev=1752588"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-3.png?rev=1752588" alt="Checkout page with &quot;Newsletter subscription&quot; checkbox"></a><p>Checkout page with "Newsletter subscription" checkbox</p></li></ol>";}s:17:"short_description";s:126:"Integrate MailChimp into your e-commerce shop to manage users&#039; subscription directly from your store. WooCommerce&hellip;";s:13:"download_link";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.1.1.zip";s:11:"screenshots";a:3:{i:2;a:2:{s:3:"src";s:78:"https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-2.png?rev=1752588";s:7:"caption";s:55:"The YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp settings page (checkout)";}i:1;a:2:{s:3:"src";s:78:"https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-1.png?rev=1752588";s:7:"caption";s:58:"The YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp settings page (integration)";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:"src";s:78:"https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/trunk/screenshot-3.png?rev=1752588";s:7:"caption";s:53:"Checkout page with "Newsletter subscription" checkbox";}}s:4:"tags";a:5:{s:8:"checkout";s:8:"checkout";s:9:"mailchimp";s:9:"mailchimp";s:6:"themes";s:6:"themes";s:11:"woocommerce";s:11:"woocommerce";s:3:"yit";s:3:"yit";}s:8:"versions";a:13:{s:5:"1.0.0";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.0.zip";s:5:"1.0.1";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.1.zip";s:5:"1.0.2";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.2.zip";s:5:"1.0.3";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.3.zip";s:5:"1.0.4";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.4.zip";s:5:"1.0.5";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.5.zip";s:5:"1.0.6";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.6.zip";s:5:"1.0.7";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.7.zip";s:5:"1.0.8";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.8.zip";s:5:"1.0.9";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.0.9.zip";s:5:"1.1.0";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.1.0.zip";s:5:"1.1.1";s:75:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.1.1.1.zip";s:5:"trunk";s:69:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp.zip";}s:11:"donate_link";s:0:"";s:5:"icons";a:1:{s:2:"1x";s:79:"https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/assets/icon-128x128.jpg?rev=1121259";}s:12:"contributors";a:0:{}}}s:23:"yith-woocommerce-stripe";a:5:{s:4:"name";s:23:"YITH WooCommerce Stripe";s:4:"slug";s:23:"yith-woocommerce-stripe";s:15:"premium_constat";s:21:"YITH_WCSTRIPE_PREMIUM";s:4:"file";s:8:"init.php";s:7:"wp_info";a:27:{s:4:"name";s:23:"YITH WooCommerce Stripe";s:4:"slug";s:23:"yith-woocommerce-stripe";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.3.0";s:6:"author";s:43:"<a href="http://yithemes.com/">YIThemes</a>";s:14:"author_profile";s:39:"https://profiles.wordpress.org/yithemes";s:8:"requires";s:3:"4.2";s:6:"tested";s:5:"4.7.7";s:12:"requires_php";b:0;s:6:"rating";d:70;s:7:"ratings";a:5:{i:5;i:2;i:4;i:0;i:3;i:0;i:2;i:2;i:1;i:0;}s:11:"num_ratings";i:4;s:15:"support_threads";i:0;s:24:"support_threads_resolved";i:0;s:15:"active_installs";i:3000;s:10:"downloaded";i:75098;s:12:"last_updated";s:22:"2017-04-04 12:15pm GMT";s:5:"added";s:10:"2015-02-20";s:8:"homepage";s:59:"http://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-stripe/";s:8:"sections";a:5:{s:11:"description";s:1458:"<p>Stripe is a WooCommerce extension, that allows you to add a new payment gateway into your e-commerce website and gives your<br />\nusers the possibility to pay directly by credit card through Stripe.com checkout.</p>\n<p>Stripe is available in the United States, Canada, the UK, Australia, Belgium, France, Germany, Ireland, The Netherlands<br />\nand more – see <a href="https://stripe.com/global" rel="nofollow">What countries does stripe support?</a></p>\n<p>Stripe advantages:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&#171;Proven fraud protection&#187;, stripe actively works to protect your business from fraudulent charges and monitors suspicious transactions.</li>\n<li>&#171;Act locally, work globally&#187;, work with international customers right out of the box while still getting paid in your preferred currency.</li>\n<li>&#171;Operations, simplified&#187;, handling billing support and disputes is easy with Stripe — address issues with a few clicks, or automate it.</li>\n<li>&#171;Battle-tested systems&#187;, <a href="https://status.stripe.com/" rel="nofollow">high availability</a>, transparent uptime reporting, and always ready for high transaction throughput.</li>\n<li>&#171;Seamless security&#187;, stripe provides security and compliance without the headaches.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please, read the the <strong><a href="http://yithemes.com/docs-plugins/yith-woocommerce-stripe" rel="nofollow">official plugin documentation</a></strong> to know all plugin features.</p>\n";s:12:"installation";s:743:"<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Stripe</code> from Plugins page</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Настройки</h4>\n<p>YITH WooCommerce Stripe will add a new settings tab called &#171;Stripe&#187;, into Woocommerce -&gt; Settings -&gt; Checkout -&gt; Stripe. Here you are able to configure all the plugin settings.<br />\nYou need to register an account to <a href="https://stripe.com/" rel="nofollow">Stripe.com</a> and set the API key in the plugin settings.<br />\nYou can get the API keys from <a href="https://dashboard.stripe.com/account/apikeys" rel="nofollow">your stripe dashboard</a>.</p>\n";s:3:"faq";s:817:"\n<h4>Does this plugin support Stripe Checkout?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes it does! After user has compiled all information on checkout page, you will be redirect to payment page where there is the Stripe Checkout button and pay.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Which countries does Stripe support?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Stripe is available in many countries and is constantly expanding to more. To see if your country is supported, visit the <a href="https://stripe.com/global" rel="nofollow">Stripe Global page</a>.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Does Stripe require that my site have an SSL certificate?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes, an SSL certificate should always be used with Stripe. All pages that include a payment form should be prefixed with https://, not http://. See <a href="https://stripe.com/help/ssl" rel="nofollow">Stripe’s SSL page</a> for more information.</p>\n</p>\n\n";s:9:"changelog";s:2227:"<h4>1.3.0 &#8212; Released on Apr 04, 04</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: WordPress 4.7.3 compatibility</li>\n<li>New: WooCommerce 3.0.0-RC2 compatibility</li>\n<li>New: added italian &#8212; ITALY translation</li>\n<li>Tweak: added check over gateway existence</li>\n<li>Tweak: updated Stripe library to 3.23.0</li>\n<li>Tweak: changed text domain to yith-woocommerce-stripe</li>\n<li>Dev: added yith_stripe_locale filter to change locale used in hosted checkout</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.9 &#8212; Released on May 31, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: Support to WC 2.6 beta 3</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.7.1 &#8212; Released on Apr 11, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: missing files causing warnings</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.7 &#8212; Released on Apr 06, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: fatal error with Stripe\\Error\\API</li>\n<li>Fixed: wrong cart total on hosted checkout</li>\n<li>Fixed: internal server error if the import is lower then .50 cent</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.5 &#8212; Released on Feb 16, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: stripe library loading causing fatal error in some servers</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.4 &#8212; Released on Jan 19, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: compatibility with WooCommerce 2.5</li>\n<li>Added: language support for &#171;Stripe checkout&#187; mode</li>\n<li>Updated: Stripe API library with latest version</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.3 &#8212; Released on Dec 14, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: no errors for wrong cards during checkout</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.2 &#8212; Released on Dec 10, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: compatibility to multi currency plugin</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.0 &#8212; Released on Aug 12, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: Support to WooCommerce 2.4</li>\n<li>Updated: Plugin core framework</li>\n<li>Updated: Language pot file</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.0 &#8212; Released: Apr 22, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added: support to WordPress 4.2</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.4 &#8212; Released: Apr 21, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updated: Languages pot catalog</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.3 &#8212; Released: Apr 15, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updated: Stripe API</li>\n<li>Fixed: minor bugs</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2 &#8212; Released: Mar 04, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updated: Plugin core framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1 &#8212; Released: Mar 03, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed: minor bugs</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Первый релиз</li>\n</ul>\n";s:11:"screenshots";s:981:"<ol><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1629162"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1629162" alt="The payment method on checkout page"></a><p>The payment method on checkout page</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=1629162"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=1629162" alt="Pay page"></a><p>Pay page</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1629162"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1629162" alt="Stripe.com Checkout panel"></a><p>Stripe.com Checkout panel</p></li><li><a href="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=1629162"><img src="https://ps.w.org/yith-woocommerce-stripe/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=1629162" alt="Функции"></a><p>Функции</p></li></ol>";}s:17:"short_description";s:88:"The YITH WooCommerce Stripe plugin let you add a new payment gateway based on Stripe.com";s:13:"download_link";s:72:"https://downloads.wordpress.org/