gins/yith-woocommerce-tab-manager/";s:8:"sections";a:5:{s:11:"description";s:857:"<p>Efficient pages for direct information</p>\n<p>Understanding is vital to reassure clients and with YITH WooCommerce Tab Manager you will be able to customize the product pages with all the information you want:<br />\nPDF files to download, virtual maps, video tutorials, additional details, galleries&#8230; every kind of content! The best way to offer what users need and persuade them to purchase immediately.</p>\n<p><strong>Main features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Freedom to create infinite tabs containing an editor</li>\n<li>Options to rename, move and delete the created tabs</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For a more detailed list of options and features of the plugin, please look at the <a href="http://yithemes.com/docs-plugins/yith-woocommerce-tab-manager/" title="Yith WooCommerce Tab Manager official documentation" rel="nofollow">official documentation</a>.</p>\n";s:12:"installation";s:239:"<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Tab Manager</code> from Plugins page</li>\n</ol>\n";s:3:"faq";s:2963:"\n<h4>Installation Instructions</h4>\n<p>\n<ol>\n<li>Unzip the downloaded zip file.</li>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder into the <code>wp-content/plugins/</code> directory of your WordPress site.</li>\n<li>Activate <code>YITH WooCommerce Tab Manager</code> from Plugins page</li>\n</ol>\n</p>\n<h4>Translation issue with the version 1.1.0</h4>\n<p>\n<p>In order to import correctly the plugin strings in the new system, we had to change the text domain form &#8216;yith_wc_tab_manager&#8217; to &#8216;yith-woocommerce-tab-manager&#8217;. Once the plugin will be imported in the translate.wordpress.org system, the translations of other languages will be downloaded directly from WordPress, without using any .po and .mo files. Moreover, users will be able to participate in a more direct way to plugin translations, suggesting texts in their languages in the dedicated tab on translate.wordpress.org. During this transition step, .po and .mo files will be used as always, but in order to be recognized by WordPress, they will need to have a new nomenclature, renaming them in: yith-woocommerce-featured-video-.po yith-woocommerce-featured-video-.mo. For example, if your language files were named yith_wc_tab_manager-en_GB.po and yith_wc_tab_manager-en_GB.mo, you will just have to rename them respectively as yith-woocommerce-tab-manager-en_GB.po and yith-woocommerce-manager-en_GB.mo.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>Is the plugin compatible with all WordPress themes?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Compatibility with all themes is impossible, because they are too many, but generally if themes are developed according to WordPress and WooCommerce guidelines, YITH plugins are compatible with them.<br />\nYet, we can grant compatibility with themes developed by YIThemes, because they are constantly updated and tested with our plugins. Sometimes, especially when new versions are released, it might only require some time for them to be all updated, but you can be sure that they will be tested and will be working in a few days.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>How can I get support if my WooCommerce plugin is not working?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>If you have problems with our plugins or something is not working as it should, first follow this preliminary steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Test the plugin with a WordPress default theme, to be sure that the error is not caused by the theme you are currently using.</li>\n<li>Deactivate all plugins you are using and check if the problem is still occurring.</li>\n<li>Ensure that you plugin version, your theme version and your WordPress and WooCommerce version (if required) are updated and that the problem you are experiencing has not already been solved in a later plugin update.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If none of the previous listed actions helps you solve the problem, then, submit a ticket in the forum and describe your problem accurately, specify WordPress and WooCommerce versions you are using and any other information that might help us solve your problem as quickly as possible. Thanks!</p>\n</p>\n\n";s:9:"changelog";s:2150:"<h4>Version 1.1.9 &#8212; Released: Oct 10, 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.8.2</li>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 3.2.0-RC2</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.8 &#8212; Released: Feb 21, 2017</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New:  Support to WooCommerce 2.7.0-RC1</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.7 &#8212; Released: Dec 09, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WordPress 4.7</li>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.6.9</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.6 &#8212; Released: Aug 05, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Default WordPress editor to manage Content tab</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n<li>Fix: Text Domain</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.5 &#8212; Released: Apr 28, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.4 &#8212; Released: Mar 15, 2016</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.3 &#8212; Released: Jan 22, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.5</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.1 &#8212; Released: Jan 05, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n<li>Update: Language file</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.1.0 &#8212; Released: Dec 09, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: Language file</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin Framework</li>\n<li>Change: Text Domain</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.0.6 &#8212; Released: Oct 30, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Plugin framework loader</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.0.5 &#8212; Released: Oct 26, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tweak: Performance improved with new plugin core 2.0</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Version 1.0.4 &#8212; Released: Aug 13, 2015</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New: Support to WooCommerce 2.4</li>\n<li>Update: Plugin core f